, "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arcname", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict | list | str | Image.Image | ConfigParser", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Reads data from an internal file.\nArcname is the path of the internal file, it may include \nthe file extension.\n\nAccording to the type of the file extension found in the arcname \nthe method will decide the correct way of decoding it, according \nto the following scheme.\nIf it is:\n    - `.json`: json file.\n    - `.png` or `jpeg`: Image.\n    - `.config` or `.dat`: ConfigParser\n    - otherwise: string\n\nIf you have a different extension, that could not be inferred, you\nmay use the following explicit read methods:\n    - `read_json`\n    - `read_image`\n    - `read_string`\n    - `read_configparser`\n\nAnother option is to use the method `open`"]}, {"name": "fileboxes.filebox.Filebox.open", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arcname", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "mode", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "ZipIO", "xref": {"fqname": "fileboxes.zipio.ZipIO", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Opens an internal file from your filebox.\nThis works in a similar way to the builtin `open` funcion."]}, {"name": "fileboxes.filebox.Filebox.remove", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pattern", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Deletes a file from your filebox."]}, {"name": "fileboxes.filebox.Filebox.contains", "asynchronous": fals